k wants to take on Claude Code and OpenAI's Codex with \"Deepseek Code\"", "summary": "Deepseek is building a new team in Beijing to develop its own AI code agent, working title \"Deepseek Code,\" a direct competitor to Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor. Applicants should know agent loops, MCP, and context engineering and be heavy users of existing coding tools.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/deepseek-wants-to-take-on-claude-code-and-openais-codex-with-deepseek-code/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 9}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=35727", "title": "Stability AI launches Stable Audio 3.0 with up to six-minute tracks and open weights", "summary": "Stability AI has unveiled Stable Audio 3.0, a new generation of audio models - three of which ship with open weights. The models generate music tracks up to six minutes long and were trained entirely on licensed data, according to the company.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/stability-ai-launches-stable-audio-3-0-with-up-to-six-minute-tracks-and-open-weights/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 9}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1137523", "title": "Green steel startup Boston Metal is doubling down on critical metals", "summary": "The startup Boston Metal has raised a $75 million funding round to produce critical metals, MIT Technology Review can exclusively report.&#160;&#160; The company has been known largely for its efforts to clean up steel production, an industry that&#8217;s responsible for about 8% of global greenhous...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/05/20/1137523/boston-metal-funding-critical-metals/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 6}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=35724", "title": "Google pairs its Genie world model with Street View to create explorable AI worlds based on real places", "summary": "Google Deepmind connects its Genie 3 world model to Street View imagery: users drop a pin on a map and get a walkable,